---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<section
    class="py-24 bg-deep-space-gradient text-white relative overflow-hidden"
>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <!-- Image Side -->
        <div
            class="relative h-[600px] w-full bg-black/90 rounded-none overflow-hidden shadow-[0_0_50px_rgba(0,31,63,0.5)] border-l-4 border-blue-belt-end transform hover:scale-[1.01] transition-transform duration-500 hover:shadow-[0_0_80px_rgba(0,229,255,0.3)]"
        >
            <img
                src="/images/andrea1.webp"
                alt="Andrea Kilday Portrait"
                class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-contain object-center opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
            />
            <div
                class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2 bg-gradient-to-t from-deep-space-black to-transparent"
            >
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Text Side -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
            <h2
                class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black font-oswald uppercase tracking-tighter drop-shadow-lg"
            >
                Head Instructor: <span class="block text-white"
                    >Andrea Kilday</span
                >
            </h2>

            <h3
                class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-oswald text-blue-gradient uppercase tracking-wide"
            >
                3rd Dan Black Belt <span class="mx-2 text-blue-belt-end/50"
                    >|</span
                > Rio 2016 Olympian
            </h3>

            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 font-body">
                Andrea Kilday is not just a teacher; she is a testament to
                resilience. A dominant force in the -49kg division, Andrea’s
                journey took her to the pinnacle of sport: The Olympic Games.
                After qualifying for Beijing 2008 but facing non-selection, she
                demonstrated the ultimate black belt tenet—<strong
                    >Perseverance</strong
                >—fighting her way back to win Gold at the Oceania Qualifiers
                and representing New Zealand at the Rio 2016 Olympics.
            </p>

            <ul
                class="space-y-4 mt-4 font-bold font-oswald text-xl uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-200"
            >
                <li class="flex items-center gap-4">
                    <span class="text-blue-gradient hover-glow">★</span> Rio 2016
                    Olympian (-49kg)
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-4">
                    <span class="text-blue-gradient hover-glow">★</span> Pacific
                    Games Gold Medalist (2015)
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-4">
                    <span class="text-blue-gradient hover-glow">★</span> Oceania
                    Olympic Selection Gold (2007 & 2016)
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
